The paper presents an extension to two popular student knowledge modeling algorithms, DKT and DKVMN, which are based on deep learning techniques. Therefore, it is likely to be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also deals with natural language processing (NLP) techniques to extract interpretable knowledge from the models, which suggests a possible categorization under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper discusses the application of the models in the context of education, which could lead to a categorization under cs.EDU (Education). Finally, the paper also deals with the performance evaluation of the models, which could suggest a possible categorization under cs.CY (Computers and Society).
